# Orchestrator — Cursor Rules

## Overview
Desktop app (Tauri) that orchestrates local Spring Boot and JavaScript projects.
Two modules: `orchestrator-core` (Java 17) and `orchestrator-desktop` (Tauri + React).
The old `orchestrator-ui/` module is DEPRECATED — all frontend lives in `orchestrator-desktop/src/`.

Human onboarding: `docs/guides/DEVELOPING.md`. Integration: `docs/integration/INTEGRATION.md`. IPC: `docs/reference/IPC.md`. Scripts: `scripts/README.md`. Verify: `scripts/unix/verify.sh`.
Module indexes: `orchestrator-core/.cursorrules`, `orchestrator-desktop/.cursorrules`.

## Architecture

```
orchestrator-core/          Java 17, fat JAR, stdin/stdout JSON IPC
orchestrator-desktop/       Tauri (Rust) + React/Vite/Tailwind
  ├── src/                  React frontend (TSX)
  ├── src-tauri/src/        main.rs (commands), core_bridge.rs (CoreBridge), java_runtime.rs, java_env.rs
  └── src-tauri/tauri.conf  Tauri config
```

### IPC Flow
UI (React) → invoke("core_request") → Rust (main.rs CoreBridge)
→ stdin JSON → Java Core (CoreRuntime.handle) → stdout JSON → Rust → UI

### IPC Protocol
Request:  `{"id":"uuid","method":"methodName","params":{...}}`
Response: `{"id":"uuid","ok":true,"result":{...},"error":null}`
Event:    `{"event":"eventName","payload":{...}}` (emitted as core_event to UI)

## Core Module (Java 17)

### Key Classes
| Class | Responsibility | Package |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| Main | Entry point, reads stdin, dispatches to CoreRuntime | core |
| CoreRuntime | Method dispatch, lifecycle | core.runtime |
| WorkspaceManager | Roots, scan, persistence | core.runtime |
| WorkspaceDefinitionSync | Após scan: reaplica port/MVN no Spring; preserva java/script por serviço | core.runtime |
| MavenLaunchCommands | Windows: `./mvnw` → `mvnw.cmd` absoluto | process |
| ServiceManager | Start/stop/restart, status refresh | core.runtime |
| ContainerManager | Container CRUD, service linking | core.runtime |
| LogManager | Log subscriptions, emit lines | core.runtime |
| ProjectScanner | Walk dirs, find pom.xml, detect Spring Boot | core.runtime |
| JsProjectScanner | Walk dirs, find package.json; ignora dirs PHP (`composer.json` + artisan/symfony); Angular/React/Vue/Next/Nest | core.runtime |
| StandaloneJsScanner | HTML sem package.json (`STATIC_HTML`); `.js` avulso (`STANDALONE_JS`) | core.runtime |
| JsLaunchCommands | `npm run`, `npx serve`, `node file.js`; portas e `applySelection` | core.runtime |
| PhpProjectScanner | `composer.json`; Laravel/Symfony/Composer; ignora dirs com `pom.xml` | core.runtime |
| StandalonePhpScanner | `index.php` sem manifest (`STANDALONE_PHP`) | core.runtime |
| PhpLaunchCommands | `artisan serve`, `composer run`, `symfony server`, `php -S` | core.runtime |
| PhpVersionDetector | PHP no PATH, Homebrew, phpenv | process |
| PortExtractor | Read port from application.properties/yml | core.runtime |
| ExternalToolLauncher | Open folder/terminal/editor | core.runtime |
| StateStore | JSON read/write to files | core.runtime |
| ProcessManager | Process start/stop/kill, alive check | process |
| JavaVersionDetector | JDKs: SDKMAN, Homebrew, Program Files (Windows), macOS JVMs, JAVA_HOME | process |

### Models
| Model | Type | Package | Role |
|-------|------|---------|------|
| Workspace | Lombok @Data | model | Aggregate root (roots, services, containers) |
| ServiceDefinition | Lombok @Data | model | Persisted service config |
| ServiceView | Record | model | Read model / IPC DTO |
| ServiceDescriptor | Lombok @Data | model | Definition + runtime pair (in-memory) |
| Container | Lombok @Data | model | Logical service group |

### IPC Methods (CoreRuntime.handle)
Full table with client.ts mapping: `docs/reference/IPC.md`. Integration flow: `docs/integration/INTEGRATION.md`. Key groups:
- workspace: ping, getWorkspace, setExcludeDirs, importRootAndScan, importRootsAndScan, removeRoot, scanRoots
- services: listServices, listServiceBranches, start/stop/restart, startAll/stopAll, removeService, reorderServices
- logs: subscribeLogs, unsubscribeLogs
- containers: create/update/delete/list, add/remove service, getServicesByContainer, start/stop container, reorderContainers
- tools: openServiceFolder, openServiceTerminal, openServiceInEditor
- java: listJdks, getActiveJavaInfo, setServiceJavaVersion, setServiceMvnWrapper, rebuildServices
- php: listPhpRuntimes, getActivePhpInfo, setServicePhpVersion
- js/spring config: setServiceScript, setServicePort, resetServicePort
- ports: checkPortFree, killPort

### Persistence
- `workspace.json` — roots, services, containers, removedServices (exclusion set)
- `runtime.json` — per-service runtime state (pid, status, timestamps)
- Both in `--stateDir` directory

### Critical Business Rules
- Container deletion NEVER removes services — only clears containerIds
- scanRoots() preserves existing containerIds by merging on service name
- Stale containerIds (referencing deleted containers) are cleaned during scan
- Removed services tracked in `workspace.removedServices`; excluded from scan
- importRootAndScan clears removedServices when adding a new root
- importRootsAndScan: folders with pom.xml added as direct services, others as roots
- Service removal clears containerIds before removing
- Ports auto-detected from application.properties/yml, fallback to hash-based
- JS services keep `detectedPort` only for UI; only scripts com `portStrategy=CLI` aceitam `customPort`. `listServices` re-lê `package.json` para sincronizar scripts/porta/strategy

## Desktop Module (Tauri + React)

### Rust (src-tauri/src/)
- `core_bridge.rs`: CoreBridge spawns Java JAR, stdin/stdout IPC; `ensure_started_and_send_request` segura o mutex `lifecycle` do início ao fim da requisição para não conflitar com `cleanup` (troca do Java nas Configurações)
- `java_runtime.rs`: PATH/JAVA_HOME merge, `spawn_core`, stderr log `desktop-logs/core.stderr.log`
- `java_env.rs`: Java 17+ check (`java -version` parse), `CREATE_NO_WINDOW` on Windows, reject Microsoft Store stub paths (`WindowsApps`)
- `main.rs`: Tauri commands (`core_request`, settings, folder dialogs)
- Windows: disable Store aliases for `java.exe` if `-version` output is empty; prefer `JAVA_HOME` or Settings JDK path (Temurin 17+)
- Events emitted as "core_event" to UI

### React Components
Full map: `orchestrator-desktop/src/ui/README.md`. Main: App, Toolbar, ServiceTable, ContainersPanel, ContainerTabs, LogsPanel, MonitorPanel, SettingsPanel, ContextMenu, KillPortModal, ServicePortModal. Hooks: useCoreEvents, useServiceBranchPolling, useJavaRuntime, useServiceShortcuts, useDragReorder.

### API Client (api/client.ts)
- `core()` serializa chamadas a `invoke("core_request")` numa fila (evita vários IPC em paralelo no Windows)
- Types in `api/types.ts`: ServiceDto, ContainerDto, WorkspaceDto, StopResultDto
- Branch atual é buscada por polling via `listServiceBranches` e mesclada no estado do React

### Keyboard Shortcuts
- Ctrl+S: start selected service
- Ctrl+X: stop selected service
- Ctrl+R: restart selected service
- Ctrl+F: search in logs

## Build
- `scripts/unix/build.sh` — full build: core JAR → copy to Tauri → frontend build → Tauri build (macOS/Linux/Git Bash)
- `scripts/windows/build.ps1` / `build.cmd` — mesmo fluxo no Windows; `build.cmd` chama `vcvars64.bat` (MSVC) quando existir Build Tools 2022, depois PowerShell com `ExecutionPolicy Bypass`; após mover a pasta do repo, se o Tauri falhar com caminho antigo em `target\`, use `build.cmd -CleanTauriTarget` ou `ORCHESTRATOR_CLEAN_TAURI_TARGET=1`
- `scripts/windows/build.ps1` antepõe `%LOCALAPPDATA%\OrchestratorBuildDeps` (Maven/Node portáteis se existirem), resolve `mvn`/`npm`/`cargo` via PATH, `MAVEN_HOME`, ou caminhos comuns; falha de passo propaga exit code
- `scripts/unix/start.sh` (macOS/Linux) ou **`scripts/windows/start.cmd` / `start.ps1`** (Windows) — ambos delegam ao `orchestrator-desktop/scripts/run-dev.mjs`; mantenha `devUrl` em `http://127.0.0.1:5173` e o Vite em `--host 127.0.0.1` para não travar o `tauri dev`
- Bootstrap Windows fica em `scripts/windows/ensure-build-deps.ps1`; instala Java 17+, Maven e Node em `%LOCALAPPDATA%\OrchestratorBuildDeps`, remove bloqueios de download e pode persistir `JAVA_HOME`/`MAVEN_HOME`/`Path`
- Bootstrap macOS/Linux fica em `scripts/unix/ensure-build-deps.sh`; instala Java 17+, Maven e Node em `~/.local/share/OrchestratorBuildDeps`, pode persistir `JAVA_HOME`/`MAVEN_HOME`/`PATH`, e é usado por `scripts/unix/start.sh`, `scripts/unix/build.sh` e `scripts/install/install.sh`
- `scripts/install/install.sh` — install automático para macOS/Linux via release latest
- `scripts/install/install.ps1` — install automático para Windows via release latest
- Output: `.app`/`.dmg` in `orchestrator-desktop/src-tauri/target/release/bundle/`

## Runtime Requirements
- Released desktop app bundles the core JAR but still launches it with system `java`
- End-user machine must have Java 17+ available on `PATH`
- `JAVA_HOME` is the recommended default JDK for Spring Boot services
- If `java` is not found, the desktop Settings panel can persist a custom Java home or `java.exe` path
- End users do not need Rust, Maven, or Node.js to open the desktop app itself
- Node.js and Maven are only needed when imported services depend on them or when developing the repo

## Tech Stack
- Java 17 (Maven, Jackson, Lombok for models)
- Rust (Tauri 2.x)
- React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- No Spring Boot in core (plain Java + Jackson)

## Conventions
- Ao finalizar alterações no repo, **sempre** executar `scripts/unix/verify.sh` (ou os três passos: `mvn compile`, `cargo check`, `npm run build`; corrigir até passar)
- Container = logical group of services (NOT Docker)
- Service = Spring Boot project discovered via pom.xml scan
- All IPC is synchronous request/response except log events (async stream); `core_bridge` usa **`session` Mutex** único: `ensure_started` + escrita stdin + `recv` + `cleanup` na mesma exclusão mútua (sem corridas com `set_java_runtime_path` / timeout); timeout de recv **mata** o JVM e limpa `pending`; **uma retentativa** em `CORE_SHUTDOWN` ou erros de transporte. Reader do stdout do core deve usar **`read_until` + `from_utf8_lossy`** (não `lines().flatten()`) para não perder respostas com bytes inválidos. Eventos `core_event`: `async_runtime::spawn` + emit. Core **não** sobe no `.setup` do Tauri. **`scripts/windows/start.cmd`** zera `ORCHESTRATOR_SKIP_MVN_CLEAN` antes do PS1 para forçar rebuild; **`run-dev.mjs`**: Maven default **`clean package`** (skip clean só com `ORCHESTRATOR_SKIP_MVN_CLEAN=1`). Smoke: `npm run verify:core-ipc`
- Windows runtime: `java_runtime.rs` tenta JDK local em `%LOCALAPPDATA%\OrchestratorBuildDeps` antes do PATH; `MavenLaunchCommands` resolve `mvn.cmd` por `MAVEN_HOME`, `PATH` e deps locais
- Unix runtime: `java_runtime.rs` também tenta JDK local em `~/.local/share/OrchestratorBuildDeps` antes do PATH
- State persisted as JSON files, no database
- Max 300 lines per file
- No comments in code
- Portuguese for UI text, English for code identifiers
